# ============================================================
# aiCRO — open-source repo hygiene
#
# THE LOAD-BEARING RULE: real client engagements live in companies/
# and MUST NEVER be committed. The pipeline keeps writing there locally;
# git never sees it. The clonable example is demo/ (a fictional company),
# which IS committed.
# ============================================================

# --- Client data — never commit anything under companies/ -----------
# Ignore the whole tree, then un-ignore only the explanatory stub so the
# folder exists in the repo with instructions but zero client content.
/companies/*
!/companies/README.md
!/companies/.gitkeep

# Shipped client zips
/dist/

# --- Operator-internal scratch anywhere (defense in depth) ----------
# Even if a _work/ dir appears outside companies/, never commit it.
**/_work/

# --- OS / editor cruft ----------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- Finder duplicate slips -----------------------------------------
* 2.html
* 2.css
* 2.js
* 2.md
* 2/

# --- Browser/QA audit artifacts -------------------------------------
.gstack/
**/.gstack/

# --- Internal scouting digests of a real prior engagement -----------
# These predate the client-anonymity hardening and reference real client
# identifiers; keep them local, never publish.
/process/research/design-critique.md
/process/research/legacy-pipeline-brief.md
